   "source": [
    "# Localization with RBallLike\n",
    "\n",
    "`rball` provides a 3ML plugin that can perform localization of point sources.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "First we need to read in the database."

   "source": [
    "from astromodels import Powerlaw, PointSource, Model, Log_uniform_prior, Uniform_prior\n",
    "from threeML import BayesianAnalysis, DataList\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "from rball import ResponseDatabase, RBallLike\n",
    "from rball.utils import get_path_of_data_file\n",
    "import h5py\n",
    "\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "a65f0f4d",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.418295Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.417690Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.511593Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.510671Z"
    },
    "lines_to_next_cell": 2
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "file_name = get_path_of_data_file(\"demo_rsp_database.h5\")\n",
    "\n",
    "with h5py.File(file_name, \"r\") as f:\n",
    "\n",
    "    # the base grid point matrices\n",
    "    # should be an (N grid points, N ebounds, N monte carlo energies)\n",
    "    # numpy array\n",
    "\n",
    "    list_of_matrices = f[\"matrix\"][()]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # theta and phi are the\n",
    "    # lon and lat points of\n",
    "    # the matrix database in radian\n",
    "\n",
    "    theta = f[\"theta\"][()]\n",
    "\n",
    "    phi = f[\"phi\"][()]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # the bounds of the response\n",
    "\n",
    "    ebounds = f[\"ebounds\"][()]\n",
    "\n",
    "    mc_energies = f[\"mc_energies\"][()]\n",
    "\n",
    "    rsp_db = ResponseDatabase(\n",
    "        list_of_matrices=list_of_matrices,\n",
    "        theta=theta,\n",
    "        phi=phi,\n",
    "        ebounds=ebounds,\n",
    "        monte_carlo_energies=mc_energies,\n",
    "    )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0fad89c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can create an RBallLike from normal PHA files. We will use a simulated spectrum that comes from a position on the sky (RA: 150 Dec: 0) with a power law spectrum."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "5d4b3a2c",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.548734Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.516033Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.565466Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.565966Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[\u001b[32mINFO    \u001b[0m]\u001b[32m Auto-probed noise models:\u001b[0m\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [

    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[\u001b[32mINFO    \u001b[0m]\u001b[32m - observation: poisson\u001b[0m\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[\u001b[32mINFO    \u001b[0m]\u001b[32m - background: None\u001b[0m\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "demo_plugin = RBallLike.from_ogip(\n",
    "    \"demo\",\n",
    "    observation=get_path_of_data_file(\"demo.pha\"),\n",
    "    spectrum_number=1,\n",
    "    response_database=rsp_db,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1ff93992",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Fitting for the localization\n",
    "\n",
    "We will create a 3ML point source and assign priors to the spectral parameters. The ```RBallLike``` plugin automatically assigns uniform spherical priors to the sky position. This can always be altered in the model\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "0e67a575",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.575364Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.574775Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.578859Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.578114Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "source_function = Powerlaw(K=1, index=-2, piv=100)\n",
    "\n",
    "source_function.K.prior = Log_uniform_prior(lower_bound=1e-1, upper_bound=1e1)\n",
    "source_function.index.prior = Uniform_prior(lower_bound=-4, upper_bound=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "ps = PointSource(\"ps\", 150.0, 1.0, spectral_shape=source_function)\n",
    "\n",
    "model = Model(ps)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "0d17d66f",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.584188Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.582422Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.591353Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2021-10-27T07:44:34.591842Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[\u001b[32mINFO    \u001b[0m]\u001b[32m freeing the position of demo and setting priors\u001b[0m\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ba = BayesianAnalysis(model, DataList(demo_plugin))"
   ]
  },
